   147→ * `Pattern<a>` is the generic type for patterns matching a value of type `a`. A pattern can be any (nested) javascript value.
   148→ *
   149→ * They can also be wildcards, like `P._`, `P.string`, `P.number`,
   150→ * or other matchers, like `P.when(predicate)`, `P.not(pattern)`, etc.
   151→ *
   152→ * [Read the documentation for `P.Pattern` on GitHub](https://github.com/gvergnaud/ts-pattern#patterns)
   153→ *
   154→ * @example
      → …
